DataElement.preferredName: Electrophoresis Gel Gel Warping Algorithm Map java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A gel matrix through which molecules are separated, usually by size or charge, under the influence of an electrical field._A computer-implemented image processing method and apparatus for normalizing gel electrophoresis images. The method includes the steps of assigning tiepoints in a reference image and in one or more object images. The tiepoints in the object image are evaluated by comparison to a corresponding tiepoint in the reference image, and the location of the tiepoint in the object image is adjusted by slight movement to a location with respect to recognizable features in both the reference and object image. Warping functions are generated and then globally optimized.:A usually 2-dimensional diagrammatic representation of an object or area._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
